      <h1>ABOUT THE INTERVIEW WITH HENRI LAVRILLAT:</h1>
      <p>     
      Henri Lavrillat’s memories around Second World War, basically the Compulsory Work Service “STO” (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Service_du_travail_obligatoire" target="_blank">Service du Travail Obligatoire</a>) in Bordeaux and on Cap Ferret. He talks about how the bunkers in Cap Ferret - I have been taking photos of for my project "Disappearance" since 2005 - were constructed; he refers to my work in regard to his history on site, the state of the bunkers in the "here and now" and of course how it all started. (<a href="/foukauld/">Foukauld-La Disparition</a>).
